# scrub-public-repos.txt.example
#
# Copy to ~/.scrub-public-repos.txt and edit with the substrings of YOUR public
# repo URLs. The pre-commit hook only enforces scrubbing on repos whose
# `git remote get-url origin` contains one of these substrings.
#
# One substring per line. # comments allowed. Empty lines ignored.
# Match is plain substring (no regex), case-sensitive.

# Examples (replace with your real public repos):
#youraccount/your-public-repo
#youraccount/another-public-repo
#youraccount/your-website
